1
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:34,938
"Wooju Bakery."

2
00:00:46,522 --> 00:00:48,063
What the… when did you wake up?

3
00:00:50,022 --> 00:00:51,688
Why are you sleeping in my room?

4
00:00:57,397 --> 00:00:59,855
I had a nightmare last night.

5
00:01:03,147 --> 00:01:06,730
Then why didn't you wake me up? Why were
you just staring at me?

6
00:01:06,855 --> 00:01:12,480
You looked so peaceful when you were
asleep.

7
00:01:12,605 --> 00:01:14,188
And…

8
00:01:14,313 --> 00:01:15,063
And what?

9
00:01:15,188 --> 00:01:16,438
You looked beautiful.

10
00:01:17,188 --> 00:01:20,230
What are you talking about…

11
00:01:20,938 --> 00:01:22,397
My face?

12
00:01:24,105 --> 00:01:27,105
You know, don't call me 'Boss' anymore.

13
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:29,188
Just call me Wooju.

14
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:30,855
Why?

15
00:01:34,272 --> 00:01:36,938
I don't know… you keep calling me 'Boss'.

16
00:01:37,063 --> 00:01:38,855
It makes it feel like we're only connected
by money.

17
00:01:38,980 --> 00:01:42,855
But isn't that exactly what we are?

18
00:01:46,313 --> 00:01:47,480
Listen to me.

19
00:01:47,605 --> 00:01:50,647
Don't call me 'Boss' ever again.

20
00:01:51,605 --> 00:01:52,813
Got it?

21
00:01:58,188 --> 00:01:59,730
Wow.

22
00:02:02,022 --> 00:02:05,355
The bread looks really tasty.

23
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:08,605
My prince is a really good baker, so…

24
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:13,230
You know… I'm curious.

25
00:02:14,230 --> 00:02:16,772
How did the prince become such a good
baker?

26
00:02:16,897 --> 00:02:20,230
A prince doesn't usually bake bread in his
own palace, right?

27
00:02:21,147 --> 00:02:23,980
Well, when he was a boy, he used to eat
this delicious bread.

28
00:02:24,105 --> 00:02:26,105
And he wanted to learn how to make it.

29
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:29,022
So the King ordered the best royal pastry
chef in the kingdom.

30
00:02:29,147 --> 00:02:30,272
To teach him how to bake.

31
00:02:30,397 --> 00:02:33,897
Oh, so he had a teacher, huh?

32
00:02:34,022 --> 00:02:36,355
He was his his best friend, but then…

33
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,105
he disappeared.

34
00:02:38,522 --> 00:02:41,063
Disappeared? Where?

35
00:02:41,188 --> 00:02:42,480
I don't know.

36
00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:47,772
Hey! Don't touch the bread!

37
00:02:47,897 --> 00:02:50,355
And keep your drool to yourselves. These
are for the customers.

38
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:51,813
I didn't touch the bread.

39
00:02:51,938 --> 00:02:54,022
Then don't get so close.

40
00:03:01,688 --> 00:03:02,855
Everyone.

41
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:05,063
Let's work hard and sell out today!

42
00:03:06,397 --> 00:03:07,563
What's with you?

43
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:10,147
You're not the boss, what are you doing?

44
00:03:10,272 --> 00:03:12,897
It's called taking initiative.

45
00:03:13,022 --> 00:03:14,897
Taking initiative?

46
00:03:15,272 --> 00:03:16,063
Hey.

47
00:03:16,188 --> 00:03:17,772
You guys are just here to pay off your
debts.

48
00:03:18,313 --> 00:03:21,272
What initiative?

49
00:03:22,647 --> 00:03:26,480
"Don't call me 'Boss', call me Wooju."

50
00:03:27,605 --> 00:03:31,688
Who said that?

51
00:03:35,313 --> 00:03:38,272
That's only for when it's just the two of
us…

52
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:45,480
Thanks.

53
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:55,522
So you're saying aliens kidnapped you?

54
00:03:55,647 --> 00:03:58,063
I'm telling you, it's true!

55
00:03:58,647 --> 00:04:00,563
When did this happen? I'm not even sure.

56
00:04:00,688 --> 00:04:03,397
I told you, I was kidnapped! My hands and
feet were tied.

57
00:04:03,522 --> 00:04:05,313
And they wrapped me up in plastic wrap…

58
00:04:05,438 --> 00:04:08,147
Oh! And I even called the police.

59
00:04:08,272 --> 00:04:10,105
You called the police?

60
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:10,938
Yes, I did.

61
00:04:11,063 --> 00:04:12,688
And then what happened?

62
00:04:13,688 --> 00:04:15,147
Well…

63
00:04:16,147 --> 00:04:17,147
I don't really remember.

64
00:04:17,272 --> 00:04:18,522
You don't remember?

65
00:04:18,647 --> 00:04:19,980
No, it's just…

66
00:04:20,105 --> 00:04:21,688
The people who kidnapped me…

67
00:04:21,813 --> 00:04:24,563
You might not believe me, but they were
aliens.

68
00:04:24,688 --> 00:04:26,730
No, seriously, they were definitely
aliens.

69
00:04:26,855 --> 00:04:29,063
Oh, stop talking nonsense…

70
00:04:30,438 --> 00:04:32,230
Cancel that police report right now.

71
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:36,022
Hold on, I know you think I'm spewing
nonsense, but…

72
00:04:36,147 --> 00:04:37,897
- I told you!
- But I have my reasons.

73
00:04:38,022 --> 00:04:40,272
I don't like loud noises.

74
00:04:40,730 --> 00:04:41,438
Secretary Lee.

75
00:04:41,563 --> 00:04:42,772
Yes, Chairman.

76
00:04:50,188 --> 00:04:51,647
Good grief…

77
00:05:00,938 --> 00:05:02,438
Keep that video up on YouTube.

78
00:05:02,563 --> 00:05:04,355
I want him completely ruined.

79
00:05:07,147 --> 00:05:08,813
Thank you, sir.

80
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,563
Hmm.

81
00:05:19,647 --> 00:05:20,022
Ms. Mina.

82
00:05:20,147 --> 00:05:22,063
Um… please, stop investigating that
person.

83
00:05:22,188 --> 00:05:25,355
What do you mean by "stop investigating"?

84
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:28,397
About the alien thing… I misunderstood. I
was just overthinking it.

85
00:05:28,522 --> 00:05:29,813
What are you talking about? We were just…

86
00:05:29,938 --> 00:05:32,438
There's no such thing as aliens on Earth!

87
00:05:32,855 --> 00:05:34,105
It's all just conspiracy theories.

88
00:05:34,230 --> 00:05:35,522
I understand.

89
00:05:40,188 --> 00:05:43,855
Something feels off… It's like my memory
was wiped.

90
00:05:48,605 --> 00:05:49,605
Let me ask you a question.

91
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:52,605
Hmm? Let's assume aliens actually exist.

92
00:05:52,730 --> 00:05:54,855
And let's assume they're planning
something on Earth.

93
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:58,438
What would be their motive for coming
here?

94
00:05:58,563 --> 00:06:01,772
Are they here to commit crimes?

95
00:06:01,897 --> 00:06:03,563
If they're here, they must have a motive,
right?

96
00:06:03,688 --> 00:06:04,688
Think about it.

97
00:06:04,813 --> 00:06:07,938
What kind of advanced aliens would have
the motive to commit crimes?

98
00:06:08,063 --> 00:06:09,105
A motive…

99
00:06:09,230 --> 00:06:13,188
Exactly, a motive! It doesn't make sense,
right?

100
00:06:13,313 --> 00:06:14,480
Exactly!

101
00:06:14,605 --> 00:06:16,438
A motive!

102
00:06:18,272 --> 00:06:19,688
Thanks, senior.

103
00:06:20,397 --> 00:06:24,105
Geez… this guy has really lost it.

104
00:06:27,022 --> 00:06:28,480
Thank you for coming!

105
00:06:29,563 --> 00:06:30,813
Take care.

106
00:06:32,272 --> 00:06:35,813
Hey! You're that YouTuber, right?

107
00:06:35,938 --> 00:06:37,397
Come on in!

108
00:06:46,813 --> 00:06:48,063
Hmph.

109
00:06:49,105 --> 00:06:50,438
What…

110
00:06:50,563 --> 00:06:51,522
Are you here for?

111
00:06:51,647 --> 00:06:56,063
She's the one who featured us last time,
and we went viral.

112
00:06:56,563 --> 00:07:00,438
That video got 1.2 million views!

113
00:07:01,105 --> 00:07:05,147
I'm so sorry about our employee biting
your finger last time.

114
00:07:05,272 --> 00:07:06,772
I'll cover the medical expenses.

115
00:07:06,897 --> 00:07:08,188
Medical expenses…!

116
00:07:08,313 --> 00:07:09,147
Medical expenses?

117
00:07:09,272 --> 00:07:11,063
Is that all you're going to do?

118
00:07:11,188 --> 00:07:13,563
Hachi! Apologize!

119
00:07:15,397 --> 00:07:16,188
I'm sorry.

120
00:07:16,313 --> 00:07:18,063
You're a bad customer!

121
00:07:18,772 --> 00:07:19,897
Seriously…

122
00:07:20,272 --> 00:07:23,813
YouTuber… um… go ahead and start your
livestream.

123
00:07:26,605 --> 00:07:27,813
Starting now.

124
00:07:29,230 --> 00:07:33,188
Hey everyone, it's Mina from 'Publicity
TV'.

125
00:07:33,313 --> 00:07:35,147
The response to the last video was
amazing.

126
00:07:35,272 --> 00:07:36,772
So I'm back!

127
00:07:36,897 --> 00:07:39,147
Ta-da! This is Wooju Bakery.

128
00:07:39,272 --> 00:07:42,105
Honestly, this place is weird and not that
great.

129
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:44,438
But I didn't expect so many comments.

130
00:07:44,563 --> 00:07:47,355
Should I try the bread again and tell you
how it tastes?

131
00:07:49,772 --> 00:07:51,147
Here we go!

132
00:07:51,647 --> 00:07:53,105
Try this one.

133
00:07:54,438 --> 00:07:57,063
The bread looks really fancy, right?

134
00:07:57,188 --> 00:07:59,063
But how does it taste?

135
00:08:01,438 --> 00:08:06,022
Hmm… this taste… this…!

136
00:08:07,063 --> 00:08:08,313
Ah!

137
00:08:08,938 --> 00:08:09,772
What a liar!

138
00:08:09,897 --> 00:08:11,897
What a bad customer!

139
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:15,063
Air, you try a bite too.

140
00:08:15,188 --> 00:08:17,272
Oh! Please, stop messing around!

141
00:08:17,397 --> 00:08:18,647
Hey! Stop!

142
00:08:19,647 --> 00:08:21,438
Don't eat it!

143
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,897
Hey!

144
00:08:24,272 --> 00:08:25,772
What if something happens to you?

145
00:08:29,188 --> 00:08:30,022
Raon!

146
00:08:30,147 --> 00:08:32,147
What on earth did you put in this bread!

147
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,438
I heard Earthlings love alcohol…

148
00:08:35,563 --> 00:08:37,522
So I tried making alcohol bread.

149
00:08:45,730 --> 00:08:47,313
Was it too strong?

150
00:08:48,313 --> 00:08:49,605
Wake up.

151
00:08:50,105 --> 00:08:53,272
Ah… my head hurts.

152
00:08:53,397 --> 00:08:54,688
What's going on?

153
00:08:54,813 --> 00:08:58,147
I'm sorry, the bread you just ate had
alcohol in it.

154
00:08:58,272 --> 00:09:00,730
Alcohol… alcohol bread?

155
00:09:00,855 --> 00:09:03,063
I can't drink a single drop of alcohol!

156
00:09:03,355 --> 00:09:04,605
I'm sorry.

157
00:09:04,730 --> 00:09:06,813
Then try this bread instead.

158
00:09:07,397 --> 00:09:08,897
What is this?

159
00:09:09,938 --> 00:09:12,230
Hangover cure bread.
You'll sober up immediately.

160
00:09:12,355 --> 00:09:15,855
My stomach hurts so much. Can I even eat
that right now?

161
00:09:16,397 --> 00:09:19,647
You can that bread as your suppository,
don't worry.

162
00:09:19,772 --> 00:09:21,355
I've tried it once before.

163
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:24,022
Hey! Keep it down! Get out!

164
00:09:24,147 --> 00:09:26,605
I can't stand either of you.

165
00:09:26,897 --> 00:09:29,522
So our contract is over just like that?

166
00:09:29,647 --> 00:09:31,147
Does that mean I don't have to pay you
back?

167
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:33,313
Who said you didn't have to pay me back?

168
00:09:33,438 --> 00:09:34,438
Just get out of my sight for now.

169
00:09:34,563 --> 00:09:36,980
Get out for an hour and then come back!

170
00:09:37,897 --> 00:09:38,647
Hachi!

171
00:09:38,772 --> 00:09:40,272
Break time.

172
00:09:41,188 --> 00:09:42,022
Let's go out for a bit.

173
00:09:42,147 --> 00:09:43,647
Wait a second…

174
00:09:45,355 --> 00:09:46,897
Good grief…

175
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:57,105
Are you okay?

176
00:10:14,355 --> 00:10:15,563
Hmm?

177
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:19,480
What is this? I'm actually sober.

178
00:10:19,605 --> 00:10:21,063
Really?

179
00:10:22,522 --> 00:10:24,438
I'm really sorry.

180
00:10:29,897 --> 00:10:31,813
Is this supposed to be fun?

181
00:10:33,188 --> 00:10:34,730
You don't think it's fun?

182
00:10:35,105 --> 00:10:37,605
Why would it be fun to go back and forth
like this?

183
00:10:37,730 --> 00:10:39,355
What's the concept of this equipment?

184
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,605
Are you trying to make me feel gravity?

185
00:10:46,938 --> 00:10:48,563
Isn't it amazing?

186
00:10:48,688 --> 00:10:51,355
Earthlings play like this when they're
kids.

187
00:10:59,022 --> 00:11:00,480
Prince!

188
00:11:00,855 --> 00:11:03,480
Studying the Earthlings isn't our mission.

189
00:11:03,605 --> 00:11:05,980
- Mission?
- What did you just say when you seduced me?

190
00:11:06,105 --> 00:11:08,272
You said you were going to Earth for a
special mission.

191
00:11:08,397 --> 00:11:10,980
Not running away from that arranged
marriage.

192
00:11:11,105 --> 00:11:12,855
That's what you said, right?

193
00:11:15,688 --> 00:11:18,105
Well, actually…

194
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:19,438
Was it all a lie?

195
00:11:19,563 --> 00:11:20,730
It's not exactly a lie…

196
00:11:20,855 --> 00:11:22,147
Prince, tell me!

197
00:11:22,272 --> 00:11:25,022
Did you just use me to run away from that
marriage?

198
00:11:25,147 --> 00:11:25,938
I mean…

199
00:11:26,063 --> 00:11:27,605
What are we even doing here?

200
00:11:27,730 --> 00:11:29,647
Why did we come here?

201
00:11:32,355 --> 00:11:35,813
Exactly, that's what I'd like to know.

202
00:11:37,397 --> 00:11:38,480
Welcome to Earth!

203
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:39,105
Do we know each other?

204
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:42,230
Prince! He's the owner of the exchange
shop who cheated us!

205
00:11:42,355 --> 00:11:46,272
He exchanged our money from the sale of
the two buildings only for 115,000 won!

206
00:11:46,397 --> 00:11:48,772
That's called an exchange rate.

207
00:11:51,522 --> 00:11:52,730
Thank you very much.

208
00:11:52,855 --> 00:11:57,313
Someone has been looking for you.
Follow me, quietly.

209
00:12:01,563 --> 00:12:03,230
My name is Lee Sung-ryong.

210
00:12:03,355 --> 00:12:05,522
I run a small business here on Earth.

211
00:12:05,647 --> 00:12:06,938
Nice to meet you.

212
00:12:09,688 --> 00:12:11,438
You've come a long way. You must be
exhausted.

213
00:12:11,563 --> 00:12:13,480
Yes, we've come such a long way.

214
00:12:13,605 --> 00:12:15,188
But…

215
00:12:16,272 --> 00:12:18,355
What do you do for a living?

216
00:12:19,938 --> 00:12:21,688
I am a Prin…

217
00:12:24,188 --> 00:12:27,897
I'm the Bread King.

218
00:12:28,772 --> 00:12:32,230
Why would business people come all the way
to Earth?

219
00:12:32,355 --> 00:12:34,063
The bread on Earth isn't even that good.

220
00:12:40,022 --> 00:12:42,980
I… I'll give you back the money I took.

221
00:12:43,105 --> 00:12:44,313
Huh?

222
00:12:44,938 --> 00:12:48,063
I can't let that bakery go under.

223
00:12:48,605 --> 00:12:49,855
Let's step outside and talk.

224
00:12:50,438 --> 00:12:52,480
Wait, that hurts! Let go of me!

225
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,147
Don't move!

226
00:12:55,772 --> 00:12:57,063
It's the police!

227
00:12:57,563 --> 00:12:58,605
Ms. Mina.

228
00:12:58,730 --> 00:13:00,855
The aliens tried to kidnap you again,
didn't they?

229
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:02,480
- No, that's not it.
- That's not what happened.

230
00:13:02,605 --> 00:13:04,647
Look, it's really not like that…

231
00:13:07,313 --> 00:13:09,063
Chairman Lee Sung-ryong.

232
00:13:09,522 --> 00:13:11,938
We received a report that you are an
alien.

233
00:13:12,063 --> 00:13:13,730
We're here to investigate.

234
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:20,563
Aliens? What are you talking about?

235
00:13:20,688 --> 00:13:22,772
We came here because we have the facts.

236
00:13:25,063 --> 00:13:27,647
Who filed such a ridiculous report?

237
00:13:27,772 --> 00:13:29,730
Aliens only exist in sci-fi movies.

238
00:13:29,855 --> 00:13:32,855
How could there be aliens on Earth?

239
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,022
Right?

240
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:36,022
Everyone, hands up! Against the wall!

241
00:13:36,147 --> 00:13:37,355
Move it!

242
00:13:38,772 --> 00:13:44,938
You look busy, so we'll be going now.

243
00:13:45,063 --> 00:13:47,438
We have bread to bake.

244
00:13:56,313 --> 00:13:57,522
Run!

245
00:14:55,647 --> 00:14:56,813
What's wrong now?

246
00:14:56,938 --> 00:14:59,730
The power unit and communication device
are not working.

247
00:14:59,855 --> 00:15:00,522
Really?

248
00:15:00,647 --> 00:15:04,813
The power unit and communication unit of
the spaceship are also broken.

249
00:15:04,938 --> 00:15:06,480
Shut up.

250
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:08,855
How many more days are you going to waste
on that toy?

251
00:15:08,980 --> 00:15:10,522
If it's broken, just throw it away.

252
00:15:10,647 --> 00:15:14,105
Throwing it away? Do you know how
expensive this is?

253
00:15:14,563 --> 00:15:18,230
How expensive could it be? I'll buy ten
when I get my paycheck.

254
00:15:19,188 --> 00:15:20,980
Boss, are you actually going to pay me?

255
00:15:22,313 --> 00:15:23,855
Yeah.

256
00:15:23,980 --> 00:15:29,397
I wasn't going to pay you a dime
until you paid off your debt.

257
00:15:29,522 --> 00:15:32,272
But you look a bit pathetic… No, wait.

258
00:15:32,397 --> 00:15:34,272
I'm not a heartless boss.

259
00:15:34,397 --> 00:15:36,522
I'll give you half your pay.

260
00:15:36,647 --> 00:15:37,688
Really?

261
00:15:37,813 --> 00:15:39,063
Yeah.

262
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:41,647
Thanks, Boss!

263
00:15:48,730 --> 00:15:50,563
Go clean up.

264
00:15:52,688 --> 00:15:55,272
Boss, are you gonna pay me, too?

265
00:15:56,355 --> 00:16:01,230
You'll get paid. Now go buy yourself some
clothes.

266
00:16:01,355 --> 00:16:04,730
That's a top notch pilot suit!
Not dull clothes.

267
00:16:04,855 --> 00:16:07,522
Wooju, what is this bread?

268
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:15,522
Prince, it's a Kauncilion!

269
00:16:15,647 --> 00:16:18,272
That's right! A Kauncilion.

270
00:16:18,397 --> 00:16:21,022
Kauncilion? What's that?

271
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:23,063
It's the name of our home planet.

272
00:16:24,688 --> 00:16:27,897
My dad always called it 'Star Bread'.

273
00:16:28,022 --> 00:16:31,522
Wait, you mean… your dad made this bread?

274
00:16:32,272 --> 00:16:32,772
Yeah.

275
00:16:32,897 --> 00:16:36,730
People from my place would recognize this
bread by its shape.

276
00:16:36,855 --> 00:16:40,688
Wait, your dad must be from my home town?

277
00:16:44,105 --> 00:16:48,397
Yeah, your dad is from our home.

278
00:16:49,938 --> 00:16:55,355
Why do you think my dad is from your home?

279
00:16:58,063 --> 00:16:59,772
Because…

280
00:17:02,230 --> 00:17:03,855
I know your father very well.

281
00:17:11,022 --> 00:17:13,897
You're such a liar. Do you really think
I'll fall for that again?

282
00:17:14,022 --> 00:17:19,772
Don't you dare start with that 'Prince
from another planet' nonsense again.

283
00:17:20,522 --> 00:17:21,897
I don't believe you!

284
00:17:22,022 --> 00:17:23,397
Wooju… be polite to the Prince.

285
00:17:23,522 --> 00:17:25,105
Hachi.

286
00:17:33,105 --> 00:17:35,730
I'd like one signature Moon Bread.

287
00:17:38,688 --> 00:17:40,188
Card, please.

288
00:17:42,272 --> 00:17:44,855
Sure. Enjoy.

289
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,230
Thanks for your hard work.

290
00:17:46,355 --> 00:17:47,230
Welcome!

291
00:17:47,355 --> 00:17:49,397
Can I have one Star Bread and one Moon
Bread?

292
00:17:58,647 --> 00:18:00,188
Enjoy.

293
00:18:08,230 --> 00:18:09,688
Raon.

294
00:18:10,355 --> 00:18:11,355
Yeah?

295
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:15,647
Have you really seen that bread before?

296
00:18:16,147 --> 00:18:22,230
Yeah, I ate it all the time back home.

297
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:32,105
Are you and my dad… really from the same
place?

298
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:34,480
Didn't I tell you?

299
00:18:34,855 --> 00:18:36,605
We're from the same place, that's how I
know him.

300
00:18:36,730 --> 00:18:38,438
I still don't believe you.

301
00:18:38,813 --> 00:18:40,230
You'll believe me eventually.

302
00:18:44,063 --> 00:18:46,813
Everyone, listen up!

303
00:18:47,397 --> 00:18:50,480
We have Star Bread here.

304
00:18:51,397 --> 00:18:53,730
It's the best bread in the universe.

305
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:57,563
Made by the greatest baker in the
universe.

306
00:18:58,355 --> 00:19:02,355
Many lovely people live here.

307
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,813
Friends, family, and lovers.

308
00:19:05,938 --> 00:19:07,730
And companions.

309
00:19:09,897 --> 00:19:11,980
The taste of this Star Bread…

310
00:19:19,688 --> 00:19:21,647
is the sweetness of love.

311
00:19:30,188 --> 00:19:32,147
And what about the taste of the sun?

312
00:19:33,563 --> 00:19:35,688
It's the warmth of comfort.

313
00:19:38,147 --> 00:19:40,105
And the taste of the moon?

314
00:19:45,022 --> 00:19:48,563
It's the soft, warm feeling of happiness.

315
00:19:53,147 --> 00:19:54,397
Dad…

316
00:20:59,022 --> 00:21:00,772
What are you looking at?

317
00:21:05,188 --> 00:21:06,772
The stars…

318
00:21:09,980 --> 00:21:11,522
Stars?

319
00:21:13,855 --> 00:21:20,855
My parents… they must be somewhere
out there in that starry sky.

320
00:21:33,397 --> 00:21:35,063
No.

321
00:21:36,313 --> 00:21:37,730
Huh?

322
00:21:39,855 --> 00:21:41,647
They're right here.

323
00:21:44,272 --> 00:21:45,980
In this home.

324
00:21:49,855 --> 00:21:51,897
In this room.

325
00:21:54,522 --> 00:21:56,397
Even under the covers.

326
00:21:59,188 --> 00:22:01,063
They're right by your side.

327
00:22:01,188 --> 00:22:03,855
And in every loaf of bread.

328
00:22:07,355 --> 00:22:10,105
They're always watching over you.

329
00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:22,397
Why are you looking at me like that?

330
00:22:26,688 --> 00:22:28,480
Are you…

331
00:22:33,355 --> 00:22:35,230
Are you leaving?
